Patch 0074 — every tab now has a PDF download button and a visible
3-theme selector (Dark / Light / Pro) in the header.

PDF EXPORT (components/PdfExportButton.tsx)
- One-click "PDF" button in the desktop header.
- Dynamic-imports html2canvas + jsPDF (jsPDF was already installed for
  multibagger / earnings exports; added html2canvas as a new dep).
- Captures the main content area at 2x scale, slices the canvas into
  A4-sized pages, adds a "MARKET COCKPIT · {page title}" header on
  every PDF page with route + date + page number.
- Filename auto-derived from the page <h1> + ISO date.
- Falls back to window.print() if html2canvas fails (CORS image, etc.).

THEME SWITCHER ROLLOUT
- Pulled the full 3-button (Dark / Light / Pro) selector into the top
  header bar so it's visible on every tab. Click any of the three to
  switch instantly. (The sidebar retained the compact icon-cycler too.)

Cache key not bumped — UI-only patch, no API contract change.
